d partly in Europe. Throughout its history it has acted as both a barrier and a bridge between the two continents. Turkey is situated at\xe2\x80\xa6 \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n Murat River \n Murat River ,  river, the major headstream of the Euphrates. In antiquity it was called Arsanias. The river rises north of Lake Van near Mount Ararat, in eastern Turkey, and flows westward for 449 miles (722 km) through a mountainous region to unite with\xe2\x80\xa6 \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n Ottoman Empire \n Ottoman Empire ,  empire created by Turkish tribes in Anatolia (Asia Minor) that grew to be one of the most powerful states in the world during the 15th and 16th centuries. The Ottoman period spanned more than 600 years and came to an end only in 1922, when it was replaced\xe2\x80\xa6 \n \n \n \n \n Elaz\xc4\xb1\xc4\x9f \n Elaz\xc4\xb1\xc4\x9f ,  city, eastern Turkey. It lies at the foot of a plateau overlooking a fertile plain. Originally founded as an Ottoman military garrison and administrative centre after the mid-19th century, the city grew rapidly as a result of its favourable location. Modern Elaz\xc4\xb1\xc4\x9f, surrounded by vineyards and orchards, is an important\xe2\x80\xa6 \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n Erzurum \n Erzurum ,  city, eastern Turkey. It lies 6,400 feet (1,950 metres) above sea level in a fertile plain surrounded by high mountains. On a caravan route from Anatolia to Iran, Erzurum has been a major commercial and military centre since antiquity and is now a major rail station on the route\xe2\x80\xa6 \n \n \n \n \n \n \n Article History \n \n \n \n \n Article Contributors \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n                Feedback\n             \n \n \n Corrections? Updates? Help us improve this article! \n Contact our editors with your feedback. \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n Similar Topics \n \n \n Istanbul \n \n \n Ankara \n \n \n \xc4\xb0zmir \n \n \n Antalya \n \n \n Bursa \n \n \n Edirne \n \n \n Konya \n \n \n Diyarbak\xc4\xb1r \n \n \n Adana \n \n \